  (text "UNO Q SUPER CARRIER — Rev 0.1 — BLOCK DIAGRAM\\n\\nSignal flow (IEEE 315: left→right power top→bottom):\\n\\n  J_VIN(7-24V) → [POWER] → +5V(TPS54331) +3V3(AMS1117)\\n  J_HUB(5V) → [POWER] → +5V_HUB75 (panel direct)\\n  B1/B2(JMISC/JMEDIA) → [UNO Q MOUNTING] → SPI/I2C/MIPI/GPIO\\n  [MOUNTING] → SPI → [ESP32-S3] + [ESP32-C6]\\n  [ESP32-S3] → UART → [ESP32-C6] (direct independent of UNO Q)\\n  [ESP32-S3] → HUB75 GPIO → [HUB75 DRIVER] → panel IDC\\n  [ESP32-S3] → I2S → [AUDIO CODEC] → line-out/mic\\n  [MOUNTING] → MIPI DSI → [DISPLAY CHAIN]\\n    → CBTL04GP054 switch\\n    → LT8618SX → J_HDMI (micro-HDMI Type D RPi5 compatible)\\n    → J_DSI (22-pin FPC RPi5 DSI display)\\n  [MOUNTING] → MIPI CSI → [RPi5 INTERFACE]\\n    → J_CSI0/J_CSI1 (22-pin FPC RPi5 camera)\\n    → J_GPIO40 (40-pin RPi5 compatible)\\n    → U_EEPROM (24C32 HAT ID on pins 27/28)\\n  [MOUNTING] → MPU GPIO 1.8V → [LEVEL SHIFTERS] → 3.3V\\n  [MOUNTING] → I2C → [EXPANSION] → Qwiic×2 Grove×5\\n\\nMicro-HDMI Type D: Molex 47151-2001 (RPi4/5 cable compatible)\\nC6 antenna: R_ANT_PCB(0Ω default) / R_ANT_EXT(DNP) + J_ANT U.FL"
    (at 20 270 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "945c953b-fb23-4afc-9ae7-2e0d9482e288")
  )

